The XMLD's socket manager:
--------------------------
 This part is to handle the initialization of the XMLD's
 listener sockets as written in XMLD.conf, and to deliver
 the client sockets to the socket group being checked by
 the socket selector.

API:
----
xmld_status_t somanager_init(void);

 Initialize and read conf to know about the listener soc-
 kets.

xmld_status_t somanager_shutdown(void);

 Shutdown all the listener sockets.

